result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Tyler J. Wagner was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.

miscConds.notes: Court orders $1000.00 bond be applied. Balance of costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

timeConds.notes: With Huber and Good Time Credit. Court grants the defendant 4 hours of furlough to be extended to  obtain the IID, said furlough is to be granted within the first two weeks of the jail sentence.

records.addlTxt: 11:35 am case called. Defendant Tyler J. Wagner in court with attorney Corey Chirafisi, by phone.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court questions defendant regarding personal appearance of Attorney Chirafisi-Defendant waives personal appearance of Attorney Chirafisi and court accepts waiver. Guilty plea previously entered. Court accepts plea of Guilty and enters JOC. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: 8 months WCJ, with Huber and Good Time Credit. Credit for 2 days served. To begin forthwith.  Court directs a 4 hour furlough to be extended to the defendant to obtain IID to be done within the first two weeks of the jail sentence. Court does not object to jail transfer. $1744.00 fine inclusive of costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Bond to be applied. 36 mo DL revocation, 36 mo IID effective today, OWI assessment, AODA and follow through.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given.
